	<p class="cs709C557D"><span class="cs8498B7A6">WEST VIRGINIA LEGISLATURE</span></p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">2026 </span><span class="csC2FEE544">REGULAR SESSION</span><div style="width:49pt;height:32pt;border-width:0.5pt;border-style:solid;border-color:Black;background-color:#FFFFFF;margin:0pt 9pt 0pt 9pt;padding:5pt 0pt 0pt 0pt;">
		<p class="csAC81313F"><span class="csB9803513">FISCAL NOTE</span></p></div>
	</p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">Introduced</span></p><p class="cs3E63B65"><span class="cs8498B7A6">Senate Bill 602</span></p><p class="csFF933113"><span class="csADC6E5DB">By Senators Hamilton, Azinger, Bartlett, Charnock, Clements, Deeds, Helton, and Roberts</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Introduced January 27, 2026; referred<br/>to the Committee on the Judiciary; and then to the Committee on Finance]</span></p><p class="cs29F66C3F"><span class="csEF05ACC">A BILL to amend and reenact &sect;17B-1-1 of the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended; to amend the code by adding a new section, designated &sect;17C-5-2c; and to amend the code by adding a new article, designated </span><a name="_Hlk219700741"><span class="csEF05ACC">&sect;17B-8-1, </span></a><span class="csEF05ACC">&sect;17B-8-2, &sect;17B-8-3, &sect;17B-8-4, and &sect;17B-8-5, relating to interdicted licenses and identification cards; providing definitions; establishing the application process; creating fees; providing training; providing rule-making authority; and establishing the court&#39;s authority. </span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">ARTICLE 1. WORDS AND PHRASES DEFINED.</span></h2>
	<p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csB9803513">&sect;17B-1-1. Definitions.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">The following words and phrases when used in this chapter, for the purpose of this chapter, have the meanings respectively ascribed to them in this article:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Autocycle</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &mdash; Every fully or partially enclosed motorcycle that is equipped with safety belts, rollover protection, a rearview mirror, automotive seating, a steering wheel, and equipment otherwise required on a motorcycle and which has no more than three wheels in contact with the roadway at any one time.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Cancellation</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &mdash; Means that a driver&rsquo;s license is annulled and terminated because of some error or defect or because the licensee is no longer entitled to that license, but the cancelation of a license is without prejudice and application for a new license may be made at any time after the cancelation.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Chauffeur. </span><span class="csEF05ACC">&mdash; Every person who is employed by another for the principal purpose of driving a motor vehicle and every person who drives a school bus transporting school children or any motor vehicle when in use for the transportation of persons or property for compensation.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Commissioner. </span><span class="csEF05ACC">&mdash; The Commissioner of the Division of Motor Vehicles of this state.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Division. </span><span class="csEF05ACC">&mdash; The Division of Motor Vehicles of this state acting directly or through its duly authorized officers or agents.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Driver</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &mdash; Means any person who drives, operates, or is in physical control of a motor vehicle, in any place open to the general public for purposes of vehicular traffic, or who is required to hold a driver&rsquo;s license.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Driver&rsquo;s license. </span><span class="csEF05ACC">&mdash; Means any permit or license issued by this state to a person which authorizes the person to drive a motor vehicle of a specific class or classes subject to any restriction or endorsement contained thereon.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Farm tractor</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &mdash; Every motor vehicle designed and used primarily as a farm implement for drawing plows, mowing machines, and other implements of husbandry.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs1489E706">Interdicted person</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">. &ndash; Means a person to whom the sale, offer for sale, or furnishing of an alcoholic product is prohibited by:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) law; or</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) court order.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">&quot;Interdicted person&quot; includes a person who voluntarily obtains an interdicted person license certificate under License notification or an interdicted person identification card</span><span class="csEF05ACC">.	</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">Interdicted person identification card. &ndash; Means an identification card issued under this article that:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) Bears the language &quot;No Alcohol Sale&quot;; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) Contains other security features identifying the individual as being restricted from purchasing alcohol, including a prominent red stripe on the front of the identification card.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">Interdicted person license certificate. &ndash; Means a license certificate issued to an interdicted person that:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) Bears the language &quot;No Alcohol Sale&quot;; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) Contains other security features identifying the individual as being restricted from purchasing alcohol, including a prominent red stripe on the front of the license.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Motorcycle</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &mdash; Every motor vehicle having a seat or saddle for the use of the rider and designed to travel on not more than three wheels in contact with the ground, but excluding a farm tractor as defined in this section, a moped as defined in &sect;17C-1-5a of this code, a snowmobile as defined in &sect;17A-1-1(mm) of this code, an all-terrain vehicle as defined in &sect;17A-1-1(ii) of this code, and an electric bicycle as defined in &sect;17C-1-70 of this code.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Motor vehicle</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &mdash; Every vehicle which is self-propelled and every vehicle which is propelled by electric power obtained from overhead trolley wires, but not operated upon rails.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">9-1-1 system</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &mdash; Means an emergency telephone system or enhanced emergency telephone system as defined in &sect;24-6-2 of this code.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Nonresident</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &mdash; Every person who is not a resident of this state.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Operator. </span><span class="csEF05ACC">&mdash; Every person, other than a chauffeur, who drives or is in actual physical control of a motor vehicle upon a highway or who is exercising control over or steering a vehicle being towed by a motor vehicle.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Owner</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &mdash; A person who holds the legal title of a vehicle or in the event a vehicle is the subject of an agreement for the conditional sale or lease thereof with the right of purchase upon performance of the conditions stated in the agreement and with an immediate right of possession vested in the conditional vendee or lessee, or if a mortgagor of a vehicle is entitled to possession, then the conditional vendee or lessee or mortgagor is the owner for the purpose of this chapter.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Person</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &mdash; Every natural person, firm, copartnership, association, or corporation.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Revocation</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &mdash; Means that the driver&rsquo;s license and privilege to drive a motor vehicle on the public highways are terminated and shall not be renewed or restored, except that an application for a new license may be presented and acted upon by the division after the expiration of at least one year after the date of revocation, except as otherwise provided in &sect;17C-5A-2 of this code.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">School bus</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &mdash; Every motor vehicle owned by a public governmental agency and operated for the transportation of children to or from school or privately owned and operated for compensation for the transportation of children to or from school.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Street or highway. </span><span class="csEF05ACC">&mdash; The entire width between the boundary lines of every way publicly maintained when any part thereof is open to the use of the public for purposes of vehicular travel.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Suspension. </span><span class="csEF05ACC">&mdash; Suspension means that the driver&rsquo;s license and privilege to drive a motor vehicle on the public highways are temporarily withdrawn but only during the period of the suspension.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Vehicle</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &mdash; Every device in, upon, or by which any person or property is or may be transported or drawn upon a public highway, excepting devices moved by human power or used exclusively upon stationary rails or tracks.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Wireless communication device</span><span class="csEF05ACC">. &mdash; Means a handheld device used to access a wireless telephone service or a text messaging device.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs456817A0">ARTICLE 8. Interdicted license and identification card.</span></h2>
	<h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">&nbsp;</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;17B-8-1. License notification.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) If the division receives a notification from a court as provided in &sect;17C-5-2c of this code that an individual is an interdicted person, the division:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) May accept an application from the individual for a duplicate license that is an interdicted person license certificate and, if the individual submits an application and qualifies for a license certificate, may provide an interdicted person license certificate; or</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) May accept an application from the individual for an original license that is an interdicted person license certificate; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) If the individual submits an application and qualifies for a license certificate, may provide an interdicted person license certificate.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) The term of an interdicted person license certificate shall coincide with the term ordered by the court.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) Upon expiration of the term of an interdicted person license certificate, an individual may apply for a duplicate license certificate without the interdiction restriction.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(d)(1) An individual may voluntarily apply for a duplicate or original license that is an interdicted person license certificate.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) An individual that voluntarily applies for a duplicate or original interdicted person license certificate may not apply for another duplicate or original license certificate without the interdicted person restriction for at least 30 days after the application for the interdicted person license certificate.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(e) An individual may not hold an interdicted license certificate while also holding another license certificate.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(f) The division may charge a reasonable fee to an individual to process and provide an interdicted person license certificate.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">&nbsp;(g) An individual who is designated as an interdicted person by a court is subject to the duplicate license fee and other fees necessary to administer the interdicted person license certificate.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;17B-8-2. Identification card specifications.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) If the division receives a notification from a court as provided in &sect;17C-5-2c of this code that an individual is an interdicted person, the division:</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) May accept an application from the individual for a duplicate identification card that is an interdicted person identification card; and</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) If the individual submits an application and qualifies for an identification card, the division shall provide an interdicted person identification card.</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) The term of an interdicted person identification card shall coincide with the term ordered by the court.</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) Upon expiration of the term of an interdicted person identification card, an individual may apply for a duplicate identification card without the interdiction restriction.</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(d)(1) An individual may voluntarily apply for a duplicate identification card that is an interdicted person identification card.</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) An individual that voluntarily applies for a duplicate interdicted person identification card may not apply for another duplicate identification card without the interdicted person restriction for at least 30 days after the application for the interdicted person identification card.</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(e) An individual may not hold an interdicted identification card while also holding another license certificate or identification card.</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(f) The division may charge a reasonable fee to an individual to process and provide an interdicted person identification card.</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(g) An individual who is designated as an interdicted person by a court is subject to the duplicate identification card fee and other fees necessary to administer the interdicted person identification card.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;17B-8-3. Fees for licenses.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) An interdicted person license or identification card under this article is $50.</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) A duplicate interdicted person license or identification card under this article is $30.</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;17B-8-4. Training.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">The department shall develop a training program for an authorized person to properly verify whether an individual is an interdicted person.</span></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;17B-8-5. Rules.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><a name="_Hlk219701404"><span class="cs46AE26E6">This division shall propose rules for legislative approval in accordance with the provisions of &sect;29A-3-1 </span><span class="cs1489E706">et seq</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">. of this code to implement the provisions of this section.</span></a></p><p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">ARTICLE 5. SERIOUS TRAFFIC OFFENSES.</span></h2>
	<p class="cs9A0FB74B"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<a name="_Hlk219700293"><span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;17C-5-2c</span></a><span class="csF3C8A5A3">. Interdicted license and identification card upon conviction of driving under the influence.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) After a person pleads to or is found guilty of the offense of driving under the influence as defined in &sect;17C&#8209;5&#8209;2(e) of this code, as part of a sentence for a first conviction the court may designate the defendant as an interdicted person for a time period the court finds appropriate, and require the individual to surrender the individual&#39;s driver license or identification card.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) After a person pleads to or is found guilty of the offense of driving under the combined influence of &nbsp;alcohol and any controlled substance or any other drug as defined in &sect;17C 5 2(d) of this code the court may designate the defendant as an interdicted person for a time period the court finds appropriate, and require the individual to surrender the individual&#39;s driver license or identification card. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) If an individual has a prior conviction that is within 10 years of the current conviction the court shall designate the defendant as an interdicted person for a time period the court finds appropriate, and require the individual to surrender the individual&#39;s driver license or identification card.</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to provide that a person convicted of driving under the influence may be designated as an interdicted person and is prohibited from purchasing alcohol for a certain time period.</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added.</span></p>


